title: All Types Dialog Displays Obfuscated Classes
description: The All Types dialog is displaying obfuscated classes, such as 'a,' 'a1,' 'b,' 'c,' 'd,' in JDK 1.4.
OB: The obfuscated classes, including 'a,' 'a1,' 'b,' 'c,' 'd,' are prominently displayed in the Open Type dialog.
EB: These obfuscated classes should have less prominence in the Open Type dialog.
SR:
To reproduce this issue:
1. Open the IDE.
2. Navigate to the 'All Types' dialog.
3. Observe the presence of obfuscated classes like 'a,' 'a1,' 'b,' 'c,' 'd' in the dialog.
